<h1 style='text-align:center;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto'>
Telemetered Photon Dose Trends
</h1>

<h2>ACIS</h2>

<p>
To monitor accumulative exposure effects on ACIS, we created
cumulative exposure map once a month from all observations, including cariblations,
using evt1 data of that month. This map is added on  all previous exposure
maps, and then statistics of the total exposure map is computed.
</p>

<p>
The table below lists links to trend plots of average, minimum, maximum, and 68%, 95%, and 99.7% 
level of dose for ACIS I and ACIS S.  The plots on the left are the trends of exposure doses of each month,
and the plots on rights are trends of cumulative exposure doses from the begining
of the Chandra mission (each month exposure map is added on to the
previous all exposure maps).
</p>

<p>
The second table lists the links to data tables including a link to a fits file of the month and an
image of the data.
</p>

