<hr />

<h2>HRC</h2>
<p>
To monitor accumulative exposure effects on HRC, we created
cumulative exposure maps of HRC using evt1 data of each month. 
</p>
<p>
Following steps are taken to get the results
</p>
<ul>
<li> Level 1 Event files for a specified month are obtained from archive.</li>
<li> All the extracted image data were merged to create a month long exposure map for the month.</li>
</ul>
<p>
Following plots show trend of average, maximum, and 68%, 95%, and 99.7% level doses for HRC I and HRC S.
The plots on the left are  thoese of each month, and the plots on the right are 
cumulative exposure counts from the begining of the Chandra mission.
</p>
<p>
The minimum trends are not included since the map has the grid area where has no counts at all, and
it makes the minmum counts, even it is cumulative, always zero. 
</p>

